HEADWORD: Disguiser
<hw>Dis*guis"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, disguises.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who wears a disguise; an actor in a masquerade;
a masker.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>E. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disguising</ent>⟦br⟧
